data.title: Where does Pau rank among the top international players in history?
data.meta_description: By Sam Smith | 2.10.2016 | 1:30 p.m. Pau Gasol is on the way to Toronto for the NBA All-Star Game. It’s just another highlight stop on the way to Springfield, Massachusetts and the Basketball Hall of Fame as one of the top international players in NBA history. NBA commissioner Adam Silver Thursday added Gasol to the Eastern Conference All-Star team for the Feb. 14 All-Star game to replace Bulls teammate Jimmy Butler. It will be Gasol’s sixth NBA All-Star game appearance.
